{"title_page": "Bulgy the Whale", "text_new": "'''Bulgy the Whale''' is a children's amusement ride manufactured by [[Eyerly Aircraft Company]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.flatrides.com/rides/bulgythewhale.html|title=Eyerly Bulgy the Whale|website=www.flatrides.com|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref> It consists of eight whale-shaped ride vehicles traveling in a counter-clockwise rotation, similar to a [[carousel]], while traveling up and down small hills. Although the Eyerly Aircraft Company ceased operation in the 1980s, there are still several Bulgy the Whale rides in operation. Some have had their whales repainted to resemble fish instead of whales, and others have had thematic pieces added, but the general operation and idea remains the same.\n\n== Bulgy the Whale Installations ==\nBelow is a partial list of Bulgy the Whale attractions.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Name\n!Park\n!Open\n!Closed\n!Details\n!Ref\n|-\n|Bulgy the Goldfish\n|[[Gilroy Gardens|Gilroy Gardens]]\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gilroygardens.org/play/rides/bulgy-the-goldfish|title=Bulgy the Goldfish {{!}} Gilroy Gardens|website=www.gilroygardens.org|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n|-\n|Bulgy the Whale\n|[[Lagoon (amusement park)|Lagoon]]\n|1956\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lagoonpark.com/ride/bulgy/|title=Bulgy {{!}} Lagoon|website=www.lagoonpark.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lagoonhistory.com/project/attractions/mother-gooseland-kiddieland/bulgy-the-whale/|title=Bulgy The Whale {{!}} LAGOON HISTORY PROJECT|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-18}}</ref>\n|-\n|Bulgy the Whale\n|[[Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk]]\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://beachboardwalk.com/Rides/Kiddie-Rides|title=Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk Rides for the Little Ones|website=beachboardwalk.com|access-date=2019-11-17}}</ref>\n|-\n|Bulgy the Whale\n|Skerbeck Family Carnival (Showman)\n|\n|{{yes|Open}}\n|Inc